commit.message: Only count senses at scoreable predicates
Improve the grep-ability of the Analyzer output
Use all verb PoS tags for core predications
Fix a bug in how core predications are evaluated

Fix a copy-and-paste error

Bug reported by Artsiom Artsymenia.
Support evaluation based on semantic frames and core predications
Update the scorer for the 2015 format
Create GraphReader, GraphWriter for the 2015 format
Add a tool to do a paired bootstrap test
Remove McNemar's test, which was bullshit
Harmonize the definition of 'projective' with Sagae and Tsujii (2008)
Final version for the task description paper
Start to implement new graph analytics
Add the possibility to exclude punctuation, and to treat edges as undirected
Ignore singleton nodes for most graph-theoretic properties
Fix a bug in the computation of LM, UM.
Add exact match and unlabeled scores.
Try to clarify the description of the Evaluator.
Use the evaluator (scorer) tool as an example.
Add a tool to split the training data into train/dev data according to the recommendations in our README.
Fix a formatting error in the README.
Fix a formatting error in the README.
Fix a formatting error in the README.
Add some assertions to check for valid indata.
Catch a special case where a paragraph consists of zero lines.
Added a class to compute some values that Stephan was interested in.
Added the ability to compute the number of (weakly) connected components.

issue_comments.body:
On 15 Jan 2015, at 19:37, Dan Zeman notifications@github.com wrote:

> Caused by: java.lang.IllegalArgumentException: invalid source release: 1.8

This seems to suggest that you are using a version of Java prior to JDK 8. Can you check the output of “java -version”?

M

It is 1.7: 
java -version
java version "1.7.0_67"
Java(TM) SE Runtime Environment (build 1.7.0_67-b01)
Java HotSpot(TM) 64-Bit Server VM (build 24.65-b04, mixed mode)
I thought I saw somewhere that 1.6 was required but perhaps it was Gradle's own requirement.
I suspect that this version has been installed with the last year's Ubuntu. So the scorer will not run with older Java?

On 15 Jan 2015, at 22:16, Dan Zeman notifications@github.com wrote:

> I suspect that this version has been installed with the last year's Ubuntu. So the scorer will not run with older Java?

It might work; I do not remember using any of the new language features. Try changing 1.8 to 1.7 in build.gradle and keep your fingers crossed. (It’s hard for me to try because I do not have the old JDK around anymore.)

M

Hmm, it does not: 
:compileJava
/ha/work/people/zeman/sdp-toolkit/src/main/java/se/liu/ida/nlp/sdp/toolkit/io/GraphReader2015.java:10: error: cannot find symbol
import java.io.UncheckedIOException;
              ^
  symbol:   class UncheckedIOException
  location: package java.io
Confirmed that the code needs Java 1.8. The sdp.jar file (attached as a "release" to this repository) works when run under the new Java. Closing the issue, thanks.
